  <prompt>
    Verify and integrate the canonical `<SendEmailDialog />` wrapper produced by Wave 1 task 022 into the production-shipped path of `@spaarke/ui-components`. The existing component directory at `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SendEmailDialog/` MUST either BE the canonical wrapper (re-implemented atop `<EmailComposer mount='dialog' />`) OR cleanly re-export the wrapper from `EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog.tsx`. Either path is acceptable; pick whichever leaves the smallest surface for downstream consumers to migrate.

    Empirical state (CLAUDE.md row + spec FR-03): `SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx` exists pre-R3 as a single-purpose component with a legacy `onSend` callback shape. Wave 1 task 022 rewrites it atop the engine. THIS task confirms that rewrite is shipped on the production export path — exported from the top-level `src/index.ts` barrel — and that the canonical `ISendEmailDialogProps` signature `{ open, onClose, initialTo?, initialSubject?, associations?, attachmentSources?, onSent?, onError? }` is the public surface.

    Also: produce a complete consumer audit (passed to task 053 for migration). Grep `src/` for every `import.*SendEmailDialog|<SendEmailDialog`. The known consumer is `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx` (handled by task 051). List any others in task notes for 053 to pick up.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer authoritative on the `@spaarke/ui-components` public-export contract. Familiar with `<EmailComposer mount='dialog' />` engine semantics, the canonical wrapper shape per spec FR-03, and the Wave 1 → Wave 3 transition where the canonical wrapper graduates from engine-internal to consumer-facing.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx` is the production-shipped canonical wrapper (either implemented inline or re-exported from `EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog.tsx`). `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts` exports `SendEmailDialog` and the canonical `ISendEmailDialogProps` interface. `npm run build` + `npm run lint` are clean. A complete consumer audit list is appended to `current-task.md` (and copied into task 053's notes) for downstream migration.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The pre-R3 `SendEmailDialog` shipped a legacy callback shape: parent passed an `onSend` callback that the dialog invoked when the user clicked Send. The legacy dialog also held its own send-button state and never called `sendCommunication()` — the parent was responsible for the network call. This made every consumer reinvent the request shape.

      The R3 canonical wrapper inverts this: the wrapper OWNS the send (delegated to `<EmailComposer />` engine's `send()` imperative method), and notifies the parent via `onSent` (success) and `onError` (failure with typed `SendCommunicationError`). Parents no longer touch `sendCommunication()` directly from this surface.

      Wave 1 task 022 produces the wrapper at `EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog.tsx`. THIS task confirms it is the canonical export from `SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx` (the historical import path used by consumers). The cleanest path is for `SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx` to be a single-line re-export: `export { SendEmailDialog } from '../EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog';` — preserves consumer import paths while collapsing all logic into the canonical location.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SendEmailDialog/index.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog.tsx (produced by Wave 1 task 022)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/EmailComposer.tsx (engine)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts (top-level barrel)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/communicationApi.ts (provides `sendCommunication()` + `SendCommunicationError`)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Wrapper styling MUST use Fluent UI v9 only; engine-driven; dialog chrome per NFR-03 mount='dialog' variant (compact, ~600px width).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Wrapper surfaces send-path errors via `onError(error: SendCommunicationError)` — typed ProblemDetails class, no string-only errors.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Canonical wrapper pattern (3 wrappers + 1 engine) — no NEW client-side send-email implementation; this task only confirms the wrapper is on the production export path.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-03">Canonical signature: `{ open, onClose, initialTo?, initialSubject?, associations?, attachmentSources?, onSent?, onError? }`. Legacy `onSend` callback REMOVED (consumers will migrate in task 051 + 053).</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">No direct `@spaarke/auth` import in this file; `authenticatedFetch` flows through `<EmailComposer />` props per existing shared-lib decoupling rule.</constraint>
    <constraint source="repo">`npm run build` + `npm run lint` in `@spaarke/ui-components` MUST remain green.</constraint>
  </constraints>

