  <notes>
    Integration path (A) vs (B) choice rationale: Path (B) — re-export from `EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailDialog.tsx` — collapses to single source of truth and matches the wrapper-as-canonical pattern from spec FR-03. Path (A) — inline rewrite — would duplicate the wrapper logic across two files, violating DRY. Default to (B) unless Wave 1 task 022 produced something incompatible (in which case document the divergence in task notes and pick (A) as fallback).

    This task is a FULL-rigor checkpoint because it determines the public-export contract that every R3 consumer migration (tasks 051, 053, downstream LegalWorkspace integration) will depend on. Get the export shape wrong here and every Wave 3+ migration breaks.

    The consumer audit produced here feeds directly into task 053. Do not skip the grep step — task 053 reuses the list verbatim.
  </notes>

